Due to restructuring, Kovosvit ended last year with a consolidated loss of CZK 100 million, while consolidated turnover was CZK 1.3 billion. Kuchař counts a lack of staff and shifts of subcontractors among the main problems last year. Demand for machine tools has fallen this year, down 10 to 20 percent year-on-year. "This is linked to an expected drop in turnover of the order of 10 percent," the CEO said. In 2017, Kovosvit had sales of CZK 1.3 billion and a profit after tax of CZK 40.1 million. The loss for 2016 was 719 million.
