Annex 9 / Acceptance procedure
The items below are for inspiration only.  This attachment must be accurately and comprehensively worded by the project manager.
Delivery of Upgrade
Acceptance criteria for the Upgrade Delivery to start the Acceptance Procedure
Delivery of an incremental version of those parts of the Application in the form of executable code to which the Upgrade relates
Delivery of an up-to-date version of the Functional Specification and Documentation for those parts of the Application affected by the Upgrade
Successful completion of the installation of the Upgrade on the UAT environment in accordance with the installation procedure, with the installation being carried out by an employee of the Customer assisted by employees of the Contractor
Successful demonstration of the Changes and Incidents included in the Upgrade, whereby the demonstration is performed by Contractor's employees and is deemed successful if 80% of the demonstrated functionality is performed without problems
Acceptance Criteria for Upgrade Delivery to perform the Acceptance Procedure
Successful completion of the UAT (by implementing all relevant test scenarios), with the UAT being completed as successful if the delivered Upgrade contains no more than the following numbers of pending Incidents:
Incident category TA: 0 (none)
TB category incident: 3 (three)
Incident category TC: 10 (ten)
Successful execution of business critical scenarios in a UAT environment, with no business critical scenarios having a TA, TB or TC Category Incident
The Upgrade Delivery Acceptance Procedure may also be terminated if the number of unresolved Incidents from the UAT Environment at any one time that are Application or Documentation defects meets or exceeds the following numbers of unresolved Incidents:
TA Category Incident: 5 (five)
TB category incident: 10 (ten)
TC Category Incident: 30 (thirty)
Patch Delivery
Acceptance criteria for Patch Delivery
Delivery of an incremental version of those parts of the Application in the form of executable code affected by the Patch
Delivery of an up-to-date version of the Functional Specification and Documentation of those parts of the Application affected by the Patch, where it is practical to resolve the Incident(s), these parts may also be delivered in the next Upgrade
Successful verification of resolution of the Incident(s) included in the Patch, whereby the Patch must not contain any Incidents
If the Patch has not resolved all Incidents included in it, it is at the Customer's discretion whether to mark the Acceptance procedure as successful
