Annex 13 / Contents of the works contract
1. Terms beginning with capital letters / All words and phrases beginning with capital letters, the meaning of which is not defined in this Work Agreement (hereinafter referred to as the "Agreement"), shall have the same meaning as in the contract for the provision of information system operation and development support services - Service Level Agreement, the subject of which is the maintenance and development of the Application (hereinafter referred to as the "SLA").
2. Subject matter of the Contract / Under the terms of this Contract, for consideration, at its own cost and risk, the Contractor shall carry out the work for the Customer, the exact description of which is set out in the Change Documentation (hereinafter referred to as the "Work").
3. The Contractor shall carry out the Work by the date specified in the Change Documentation.
4. Price / The Client shall pay to the Contractor the Price for the Work duly executed as specified in the Change Documents (hereinafter referred to as the "Price").
5. Payment of Price / The Client shall pay the Price to the Contractor upon acceptance of the Work, in accordance with the SLA.
6. Other Costs of the Work / The Price includes all costs incurred by the Contractor in connection with the execution of the Work. The Price also includes the cost of third party performance used by the Contractor in the execution of the Work, in particular the cost of performance of subcontractors, including authors and other external licensors, etc.
7. Default interest / If the Client fails to pay the Price when due, the Client shall pay the Contractor default interest of 0.05% of the amount overdue for each day of delay. If the Client fails to pay the Price or any part thereof due to a claim for defects in the Work, the Client shall not be in default.
8. Execution of the Work / Procedures in accordance with the SLA shall apply to the execution of the Work.
9. Acceptance Procedure / The place of handover and acceptance of the Work shall be the Customer's site. The Acceptance Procedure shall apply to the acceptance of the Work in accordance with the SLA.
10. Defects in the Work / The Work is defective if it does not have the characteristics specified in this Agreement and the Change Documents.
11. Obligation to Exchange Information / The Parties shall exchange all information necessary for the performance of this Agreement.
12. Instructions / If the Client issues a written instruction aimed at fulfilling the object of this Contract and if such instruction is not contrary to the legitimate interests of the Parties, the Contractor shall comply with such instruction. The Contractor shall advise the Client of the impropriety of its instructions without undue delay after such improper instruction is delivered to the Contractor. If it is not possible to give the necessary instruction in time, the Contractor shall act conscientiously at its own discretion and with awareness of the Client's anticipated interests.
13 Duty to co-operate / For the purpose of completing the Work, the Client shall give the Contractor all co-operation which may reasonably be required. If the Client fails to provide co-operation and as a result the Work is delayed, the delivery period shall be extended by the period of time during which the Client failed to provide co-operation.
14.Compliance of the Work with legal regulations / The Contractor shall perform the Work in such a way that it complies with the generally binding legal regulations of the Czech Republic and this Contract. The Work shall not infringe any intellectual property right of a third party, nor patent protection, trademark, copyright or trade secret.
15. Obligation to Perform the Work with Professional Care / The Contractor shall perform the Work with the utmost professional care and using, in its opinion, the most appropriate methods and procedures.
16. right to use subcontractors / The Contractor may use subcontractors for the purpose of performing this Contract. The Contractor shall notify the Client before using a subcontractor. The Client has the right to refuse the use of a subcontractor for good cause. If the Contractor uses a subcontractor, the Contractor shall be liable for the activities and outputs of the subcontractor as if the Contractor had carried out the activities itself.
17. right of control / The Client has the right to control the execution of the Work. The Contractor shall allow the Client such control. If the Client finds that the Contractor is acting in breach of this Contract, the Contractor shall, at its own expense and risk, remedy the deficiencies found. The Contractor shall have a reasonable additional period of time to do so, depending on the nature of the performance in question. This period shall run from the date on which the Client has requested the Contractor to remedy the situation.
18. Ownership of the Work / Title to the Work shall vest in the Client at the time at which the Client accepts the Work by signing the record of acceptance of the Upgrade Delivery for use.
19. Contractual penalty in case of delay / If the Contractor fails to complete the Work or to remedy defects in time, the Contractor shall pay the Client a contractual penalty of 3.3% of the Price and further 0.3% of the Price for each additional day of delay.
