More than a year ago, Mahulena Bočanová confided to Blesk that she quit alcohol. "During the holidays, I told myself that I would give my 50-year-old body a breather. I gave myself a deadline of forever. I feel terribly rested, I have a lot of energy and, most importantly, my psyche has improved. I haven't been doing well mentally lately. I'm getting up better, I don't have a headache, I have more energy, more money."
A year's abstinence is said to have been enough and the actress has found her way to alcohol again. "Sometimes I'll have a bubbly or a fine wine, but I don't drink what I used to. I'll have one drink and have fun until the morning. I might have a bottle of wine in my fridge for a week. I also like non-alcoholic beer, which I can drink anytime," boasted Mahulena, who is still a couple with Brno businessman Petr.
Bočanová has also returned to the theatre season after the holidays and will be joining the Ordinace in the Rose Garden series. "I'm ashamed of the first two performances, I was really bad, I overreacted. But it's getting better," smiles the actress critically.
