The Tenant is also obliged to insure his/her belongings against any common insurance claims such as theft or water or electric damage, within the scope of the normal household insurance.
8. Any structural alterations to the Apartment may only be carried out with the prior written consent of the Landlord in a professional manner.
The risk of such structural alteration is on the Tenant or the entity chosen by the Tenant if such alteration is made by the Tenant.
9. The Lessee may sublet the Properties or any part thereof to a third party only with the prior written consent of the Lessor.
The provisions of Sections 2274 and 2275 of the Civil Code shall not apply.
10. On the date of termination of the lease, the Lessee shall vacate the Apartment and hand it over in the original condition in which he/she took it over, taking into account normal wear and tear in normal use.
The Lessor shall be entitled to compensation in the amount of the agreed rent if the Lessee fails to hand over the Apartment to the Lessor on the day of termination of the lease until the day on which the Lessee actually hands over the Property to the Lessor.
At the same time, the Lessor shall be entitled to compensation for damages and lost profits.
11. In the event of termination of the lease by way of termination without notice by the Lessor, the Lessee is obliged to hand over the vacated Apartment to the Lessor within 30 days from the date of delivery of the written notice without notice to the Lessee.
In the event that the Tenant is in default in handing over the vacated Apartment pursuant to paragraphs 10 and 11 of this Article, the Landlord shall be entitled to compensation for lost rent with accessories in the amount of CZK ... for each day of delay.
This amount is considered by the parties to be reasonable and not contrary to good morals and not contrary to Section 2239 of Act No. 89/2012 Coll.
This amount does not exclude the Lessor's claim for any compensation for damages or unjustified enrichment.
12. The Tenant is obliged to allow the Landlord or his/her agent to enter the Apartment, provided that he/she has been notified of this at least 48 hours in advance, in particular for the purpose of inspecting the Apartment in search of a new Tenant or buyer, appraisal of the Apartment, etc.
If the Tenant cannot be present in person, the Landlord or his agent may enter the Apartment without the Tenant's personal presence.
13. The parties agree that the Tenant shall be entitled to admit new household members during the term of the lease only with the prior written consent of the Landlord.
14. In the event that there is a change in the number of members of the Lessee's household compared to the situation that existed at the time of conclusion of this Agreement, the Lessee shall notify the Lessor of this fact without undue delay, but no later than within 1 week from the date on which the change occurred.
In the event that the Lessee fails to comply with the obligations under this paragraph, this shall constitute a serious breach of the Lessee's obligations.
15. In the event that the Lessee wishes to extend the lease of the above described Apartment beyond the expiration of the proper term, then the Lessee shall notify the Lessor, or its agent, of this fact no later than 30 days prior to the effective termination of the lease.
If he fails to do so, it shall be deemed that he will not extend the lease.
Article 7 Final Provisions
1. This Agreement shall enter into force and effect upon its signature by both parties.
2. The rights and obligations of the parties not expressly provided for in this contract shall be governed by the relevant provisions of the Civil Code, unless their application is expressly excluded.
3. For delivery under this Agreement, if the addressee fails to accept a registered mail sent to any of the addresses specified in the header of this Agreement (and in the case of the Lessee also to the address of the Apartment), such mail shall be deemed to have been delivered upon expiry of a 10-day period from its dispatch.
4. This Agreement is executed in ...copies with the force and effect of an original, one copy for each party hereto.
5. All rights and obligations arising from this contract shall pass to any successors in title of both parties.
6. The Parties declare that this contract has been concluded by mutual agreement, on the basis of their free and serious will, not under duress under manifestly unfavourable conditions, and agree to its contents and in proof thereof they affix their signatures below.
