China and the US have been engaged in a trade war for more than a year, imposing tariffs on each other. The dispute between the two countries is having a negative impact on the world economy and has raised fears of a global economic recession. Washington is using tariffs to try to get Beijing to change its trade practices and reduce China's trade surplus with the US.
According to CNBC television, trade talks between the US and China are expected to resume on October 10. Its goal is to end the trade war.
