Lucie Bílá's father wasn't rooting for her at all. You won't believe what she did for a living!
Who doesn't know that national treasure Lucie Bílá (53) is originally a seamstress by profession and her own name is Hana Zaňáková, probably doesn't live in the Czech Republic. But the singer herself has now revealed that she almost worked in a glass factory!
Lucie Bílá knew from a relatively young age that she wanted to be a singer. Her love for singing was born when she was a little girl performing in the cultural centre in her native Otvovice, where she still lives.
"And I remember exactly where my mother was sitting. That's when the singer in me was born," she admitted to Impulse radio.
Her father, however, was a bit worried about his daughter's future and therefore advised her to follow the path of a craft that has a golden bottom.
"My dad always said, 'Craft girl, craft. Get your feet on the ground!' He even talked me into going to the local glass factory. The glassworks is no longer in business, but I kinda am. I'm a trained seamstress and at home I make various rosaries and pendants out of beads, which I then auction off and use the money to buy wheelchairs," she added with a laugh.
